  "text": "In the first stage, we perform back-propagation through the AE using the loss function from Eq. 24. Algorithm 2 is the back-propagation algorithm for computing the gradient of the loss function in Eq. 24 w.r.t. H. The output of this algorithm is the gradient of the loss function in Eq. 24, denoted by δ· [CITATION_1] , w.r.t. the set of filters (h c ) C c=1 shared across all layers. The number of trainable parameters is only K × C and is equal to the number of filter parameters in one layer of the network.",
